# Frontend Design System

When working in frontend files, load and follow:

- `AI skills/frontend-design-system.md`
- `AI skills/steel-signature-colors.md`

Scope:

- Applies to visual styling, components, layouts, and UI state changes in frontend code.
- Does not apply to backend-only changes.

## Global directrices

- Default to using the unified Tailwind v4 + Shadcn framework for new requested components.
- Be extremely careful about Tailwind v4 configuration behaviors (see the skill document).
- Every app shell must include a **light / dark theme control in the header** (primary top bar / `top-nav`), not only on a settings page.
- Wire it to `data-theme="light"` / `data-theme="dark"` on the document root (or equivalent single source of truth), with **system preference** as the default when no user choice is stored.

Constraints:

- Use existing Steel Signature variables (now mapped to standard Shadcn primary/background tokens).
- Maintain light/dark parity for any new UI styling.
